HEADWORD: octanucleotide
<hw>oc`ta*nu"cle*o*tide</hw>
<pr>(⟦ocr⟧k`t⟦ucr⟧*n⟦umac⟧"kl⟦emac⟧*⟦osl⟧*t⟦imac⟧d)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Octa-</ets> + <ets>nucleotide</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A molecule composed of eight nucleotide units
bound to each other by phosphodiester bonds in a linear array; <as>as, a
partial digest of DNA or RNA may include <ex>octanucleotides</ex></as>.
See <er>octamer</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

